1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:42,270
[I Don't Want to Be Friends With You]

3
00:01:50,130 --> 00:01:51,610
Look at you.

4
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:53,360
Being absent-minded at home

5
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:54,690
during the holiday.

6
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:56,200
Why don't you go out?

7
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:57,520
I don't want to go out.

8
00:01:58,660 --> 00:01:59,800
Where are your classmates?

9
00:01:59,890 --> 00:02:01,790
Don't you have any activities?

10
00:02:04,180 --> 00:02:05,450
Don't want to have activities with them.

11
00:02:05,530 --> 00:02:06,680
It's boring.

12
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,520
Who do you take after?

13
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:12,530
I remember when we
were young, your mum and I

14
00:02:12,620 --> 00:02:14,310
hardly stayed at home during holidays.

15
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:17,040
Don't you feel bored being on your own?

16
00:02:18,020 --> 00:02:19,710
Just leave me alone.

17
00:02:19,930 --> 00:02:21,560
Who else will care about you?

18
00:02:24,329 --> 00:02:25,530
Your house's such a mess.

19
00:02:25,620 --> 00:02:28,240
I don't even know where
to start the clean-up.

20
00:02:28,850 --> 00:02:29,370
Fine.

21
00:02:29,460 --> 00:02:30,760
I'm done with clean-up.

22
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:32,250
Isn't there no one to play with you?

23
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:33,250
I'll play with you.

24
00:02:33,340 --> 00:02:33,770
Let's go.

25
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:34,490
Come on.

26
00:02:34,570 --> 00:02:35,870
Go wash your face.

27
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:43,590
[Episode 11:
I'm Kind of Busy This Holiday]

28
00:02:52,460 --> 00:02:53,250
Hey, girl.

29
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:54,490
Your bike is broken?

30
00:02:54,579 --> 00:02:55,310
Here

31
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,230
let me help you.

32
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:58,630
No need.

33
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,720
No need.

34
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:01,290
You're welcome.

35
00:03:01,380 --> 00:03:02,680
Let me buy you a drink.

36
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:03,300
I'll give you a new bike

37
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:05,150
after that.

38
00:03:07,180 --> 00:03:08,570
No need, my home is right back there.

39
00:03:08,660 --> 00:03:10,310
Where are you going?

40
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:13,240
What are you doing?

41
00:03:17,180 --> 00:03:18,400
Who are you?

42
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:19,930
Who are you?

43
00:03:20,010 --> 00:03:21,290
I'm talking with her.

44
00:03:21,380 --> 00:03:22,720
Why did you cut in?

45
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:23,970
I'm her brother. What's up?

46
00:03:24,060 --> 00:03:24,810
What brother?

47
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:25,960
You want to get kicked?

48
00:03:26,050 --> 00:03:27,590
Let's see who will be kicked.

49
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:29,740
Wait,

50
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:31,160
don't fight.

51
00:03:31,329 --> 00:03:32,370
Cut the nonsense.

52
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:34,920
What do you want? We got two people.

53
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,120
Together then.

54
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:39,470
There's a fight!

55
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,600
Help!

56
00:03:40,690 --> 00:03:41,910
Is anybody here?

57
00:03:42,570 --> 00:03:43,290
Anyone can help?

58
00:03:43,380 --> 00:03:45,430
Help!

59
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:48,040
You just wait and see.

60
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:50,280
Don't let me see you anymore.

61
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:51,410
I'll beat you each time I see you.

62
00:03:51,490 --> 00:03:53,110
Don't chase them.

63
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:10,370
We've been paying the
training fee for a week.

64
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:12,090
Why haven't they called us for a training?

65
00:04:12,170 --> 00:04:15,050
I have dreamed of being
a captain these days.

66
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:16,800
I feel something is wrong.

67
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:17,730
It can't be.

68
00:04:17,820 --> 00:04:19,529
Don't we have the
address and phone number?

69
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:21,120
Let's go and have a look another day.

70
00:04:21,410 --> 00:04:23,510
The wonton here is much
better than that near our homes.

71
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:24,810
Is it tasty?

72
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:25,790
Yeah.

73
00:04:26,130 --> 00:04:28,080
Help yourself. It's on me.

74
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,410
Xiao, you are here.

75
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,490
Do you want some?

76
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:32,690
Why are you here?

77
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:34,570
What are you doing here so late at night?

78
00:04:34,659 --> 00:04:36,310
Do you know how worried we were?

79
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:38,570
Li Qing Tong and I have
been looking for you all night!

80
00:04:38,659 --> 00:04:40,730
Can't you tell us before you leave?

81
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:42,810
Are you a girl without
any sense of safety?

82
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:44,770
Why don't you go home so late?

83
00:04:44,850 --> 00:04:46,690
What if you come across bad guys?

84
00:04:46,780 --> 00:04:47,230
Get up.

85
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,640
Go home.

86
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:53,370
What do you mean?

87
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,950
Who is the bad guy?

88
00:04:55,290 --> 00:04:56,520
Slow down.

89
00:04:56,610 --> 00:04:58,050
Don't go out so late on your own.

90
00:04:58,140 --> 00:04:59,150
Wait

91
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,290
I came across Ba Dan on my way home

92
00:05:01,380 --> 00:05:02,730
and he invited me for wontons.

93
00:05:02,820 --> 00:05:04,370
I was very happy when I heard wontons

94
00:05:04,460 --> 00:05:05,450
so I followed him.

95
00:05:05,530 --> 00:05:07,160
I didn't go with others.

96
00:05:07,410 --> 00:05:08,570
Why are you so angry?

97
00:05:08,660 --> 00:05:10,480
I feared that something
might happen to you.

98
00:05:10,570 --> 00:05:11,810
I'm nervous.

99
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:12,650
You...

100
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:13,730
What are you nervous about?

101
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:14,700
I...

102
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:20,000
How could I not be nervous?

103
00:05:23,570 --> 00:05:25,050
You are not nervous at all.

104
00:05:25,140 --> 00:05:26,130
You are just angry.

105
00:05:26,210 --> 00:05:26,730
I'm not angry.

106
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:28,240
Why yelled at me then?

107
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:42,590
Are you busy?

108
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:44,790
Or I'll do it myself.

109
00:05:45,130 --> 00:05:46,200
Get off.

110
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:49,290
Why are you running around at night?

111
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:50,600
Are you out of your mind?

112
00:05:51,659 --> 00:05:53,680
Who's out of mind?

113
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:55,080
You.

114
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:56,790
You've never been smart.

115
00:05:57,010 --> 00:05:58,920
What would you do if I didn't come?

116
00:05:59,580 --> 00:06:01,200
I could run.

117
00:06:01,290 --> 00:06:02,730
How fast I can run.

118
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:04,510
Save it.

119
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,420
Chen Jun He

120
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:09,360
I once came in fourth
place in a five-kilometre run.

121
00:06:09,450 --> 00:06:10,240
If you hadn't framed me

122
00:06:10,330 --> 00:06:12,080
would I not be ranked?

123
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,570
Don't think I've forgotten about it.

124
00:06:13,650 --> 00:06:14,530
Look,

125
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:15,730
do you have to keep remembering

126
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:17,150
such a little thing?

127
00:06:17,340 --> 00:06:18,570
Why are you so mean?

128
00:06:18,660 --> 00:06:20,130
Am I?

129
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:21,640
Is it a little thing?

130
00:06:23,460 --> 00:06:25,280
Did I ever bother you?

131
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,270
Get away. I'm leaving.

132
00:06:31,690 --> 00:06:33,210
So you just lose your
temper indiscriminately

133
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:35,090
at me on the street?

134
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:36,450
You are really severe.

135
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:37,840
Do I need to report to you where I go

136
00:06:37,930 --> 00:06:39,880
and what I eat?

137
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,850
I'm telling you

138
00:06:40,930 --> 00:06:42,440
you don't need to be nervous about me

139
00:06:42,690 --> 00:06:43,990
or follow me in the future.

140
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:47,170
It's late, let me send you home.

141
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:47,610
No.

142
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:48,630
I can go myself.

143
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:00,360
Come on. Why are you following me?

144
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:01,930
I'm on my own way.

145
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:03,050
Who's following you?

146
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:07,940
Ungrateful.

147
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,430
If it hadn't been me just now

148
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:11,680
don't you know what would
have happened to you?

149
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:13,560
What would have happened to me?

150
00:07:14,340 --> 00:07:16,440
You really think you chased them away?

151
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:18,730
If I hadn't yelled like that

152
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:20,170
do you think they'd have run?

153
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:20,810
Come on.

154
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,520
Stop bragging.

155
00:07:22,610 --> 00:07:24,010
Who was so scared to hide behind me?

156
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:25,390
Now you are showing your bravado.

157
00:07:25,810 --> 00:07:27,080
Who was hiding behind you?

158
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:30,400
I'm telling you, don't follow me.

159
00:07:30,770 --> 00:07:31,870
Don't care to talk to you.

160
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:34,360
I don't care to talk to you.

161
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:41,560
Did you pave the road?

162
00:07:41,650 --> 00:07:42,840
Why can't I walk on it?

163
00:08:02,130 --> 00:08:03,550
I told them at that time,

164
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:05,000
"Go away"

165
00:08:05,090 --> 00:08:06,720
"or I will knock you down."

166
00:08:07,410 --> 00:08:08,630
Are you sure?

167
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,640
I added the last sentence.

168
00:08:13,780 --> 00:08:15,310
But it means the same thing.

169
00:08:15,540 --> 00:08:16,420
And then?

170
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:19,190
Then they were scared away by me.

171
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:21,030
You scared them away?

172
00:08:21,610 --> 00:08:23,560
Chen Jun He contributed a little bit, too.

173
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:25,290
After all, we were two versus two.

174
00:08:25,380 --> 00:08:26,640
Evenly matched.

175
00:08:26,890 --> 00:08:28,870
Why was Chen Jun He there?

176
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:30,800
How could I know?

177
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,640
By coincidence?

178
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:34,809
I don't want to criticize you anymore.

179
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:35,919
Look at you.

180
00:08:36,010 --> 00:08:37,929
Running out like this at night.

181
00:08:38,010 --> 00:08:39,490
You made Duan Xiao
go out and look for you.

182
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:41,360
He was almost speeding.

183
00:08:43,220 --> 00:08:44,440
Fuss.

184
00:08:44,610 --> 00:08:46,170
How can you call that fuss?

185
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:46,920
Duan Xiao...

186
00:08:47,010 --> 00:08:49,870
Can you stop mentioning
Duan Xiao all the time?

187
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:54,360
What happened?

188
00:08:54,580 --> 00:08:55,250
Did you two quarrel?

189
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:56,470
I scolded him.

190
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:58,910
Why did you scold him for no reason?

191
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,180
I...

192
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,270
I just don't want him
to be nervous about me.

193
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,390
It's inappropriate.

194
00:09:08,140 --> 00:09:09,730
What's inappropriate?

195
00:09:09,810 --> 00:09:11,520
You won't understand even if I told you.

196
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:16,680
I really don't know what's
in your mind every day.

197
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:17,890
But I'm telling you

198
00:09:17,980 --> 00:09:18,690
you shouldn't run out

199
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:20,280
at night like this in the future.

200
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:21,600
You understand?

201
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:24,430
Yeah.

202
00:09:25,820 --> 00:09:27,320
Go out and get me a bottle of soda.

203
00:09:28,540 --> 00:09:30,590
Insatiable.

204
00:09:32,130 --> 00:09:32,650
Excuse me.

205
00:09:32,740 --> 00:09:33,760
Hold on.

206
00:09:34,420 --> 00:09:34,880
Could you...

207
00:09:34,970 --> 00:09:35,990
Could you please fix this watch?

208
00:09:39,540 --> 00:09:41,030
What happened to it?

209
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:42,120
It's broken.

210
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:43,670
Young man,

211
00:09:43,780 --> 00:09:45,760
why are you still wearing
such an old-fashioned watch?

212
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:46,920
It's my father's.

213
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:49,740
No matter.

214
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:52,800
The watch is too old.

215
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,290
I can't find its parts.

216
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:55,550
I'm afraid I can't fix it.

217
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:56,410
What...

218
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,400
What should I do?

219
00:09:57,540 --> 00:09:58,420
How about this?

220
00:09:58,700 --> 00:09:59,970
I'll pay you 50 yuan

221
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:01,380
for this watch.

222
00:10:02,380 --> 00:10:03,370
No. I won't sell it.

223
00:10:03,860 --> 00:10:04,970
This watch doesn't even work.

224
00:10:05,060 --> 00:10:06,300
Why are you wearing it?

225
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:08,320
[Aurora Cool Play]

226
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,920
What are you going to do in the future?

227
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,050
Me?

228
00:10:11,140 --> 00:10:12,320
I'll go to my uncle's place.

229
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,280
He has a factory

230
00:10:13,370 --> 00:10:14,560
and I can go straight to work.

231
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:16,040
Bro, what about you?

232
00:10:16,130 --> 00:10:17,010
What's your plan?

233
00:10:17,780 --> 00:10:19,160
What kind of plan can I have?

234
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:20,640
Go back and look after the bathhouse.

235
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:24,840
None of us

236
00:10:24,930 --> 00:10:26,080
were admitted to university.

237
00:10:26,580 --> 00:10:27,590
No, no, no.

238
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:28,170
Me.

239
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:29,170
I was admitted

240
00:10:29,250 --> 00:10:30,320
to a junior college.

241
00:10:30,420 --> 00:10:32,090
What the hell?

242
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:33,640
We were usually at the same level.

243
00:10:33,730 --> 00:10:35,190
What kind of dumb luck have you got?

244
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,770
You two didn't learn at all.

245
00:10:36,860 --> 00:10:38,640
I learned a little at least.

246
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:40,930
It's good.

247
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:43,680
You at least won honour for us.

248
00:10:45,780 --> 00:10:47,560
How time flies.

249
00:10:48,170 --> 00:10:49,560
We are going to part.

250
00:10:50,220 --> 00:10:51,440
We won't be apart.

251
00:10:51,780 --> 00:10:52,560
The heart of us

252
00:10:52,650 --> 00:10:54,610
will always stay together

253
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:56,240
no matter where we are.

254
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,410
Let's make a deal.

255
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:58,570
When I get married

256
00:10:58,660 --> 00:10:59,770
you two will definitely be my groomsmen.

257
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:00,650
Sure thing.

258
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:01,850
You have my word.

259
00:11:01,930 --> 00:11:02,890
But bro,

260
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:03,890
when we are not here

261
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:05,480
don't make any trouble.

262
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:07,170
Don't fight.

263
00:11:07,260 --> 00:11:08,290
Don't be impulsive.

264
00:11:08,380 --> 00:11:09,730
If there's anything I can do to help

265
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:10,720
just let me know.

266
00:11:10,810 --> 00:11:12,040
Da can't come back from school

267
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:12,730
but I have no problem.

268
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:13,790
Call me and I'll be there.

269
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:14,890
No more fights.

270
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:16,290
I am too old to fight.

271
00:11:16,380 --> 00:11:17,720
It's you two.

272
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,010
Take good care of yourselves.

273
00:11:19,090 --> 00:11:20,240
Don't be bullied by others.

274
00:11:20,660 --> 00:11:22,080
If you two need help, just let me know.

275
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:26,730
It's a little sentimental here.

276
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:28,210
It should be a happy thing.

277
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:29,190
Let's play another round.

278
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:49,960
♫ We walked almost from spring to winter ♫

279
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:55,680
♫ The calendar began
to yellow under the sun ♫

280
00:11:56,960 --> 00:12:03,360
♫ We secretly competed
in the game arcades ♫

281
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:08,960
♫ The countdown has
begun for our separation ♫

282
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:16,120
♫ In a few steps we became
brothers from strangers ♫

283
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:22,520
♫ In those years we went
through many drawers ♫

284
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:29,440
♫ Can't finish talking about
long and boring topics ♫

285
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:35,520
♫ Only for a hurried
farewell in exchange ♫

286
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:42,710
♫ If I can meet you again in the crowd ♫

287
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:48,480
♫ Please don't care about our ages ♫

288
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:55,840
♫ Whenever you call my name again ♫

289
00:12:56,470 --> 00:13:02,040
♫ I won't forget our friendships ♫

290
00:13:33,430 --> 00:13:35,370
Eat some food before you drink.

291
00:13:35,460 --> 00:13:36,830
I have no appetite.

292
00:13:40,940 --> 00:13:43,120
It's okay if he didn't pass
the exam this first year.

293
00:13:43,210 --> 00:13:44,440
He can go back to school for another year.

294
00:13:44,530 --> 00:13:46,310
What's the point for another year?

295
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:50,000
Why not?

296
00:13:50,140 --> 00:13:51,330
The son of the grocery store owner

297
00:13:51,420 --> 00:13:52,610
passed the exam this way.

298
00:13:52,690 --> 00:13:53,970
He went to Xi'an for college.

299
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:55,350
What a wonderful place.

300
00:13:55,430 --> 00:13:57,690
He was originally good at learning.

301
00:13:57,780 --> 00:13:59,170
A second chance worked for him.

302
00:13:59,260 --> 00:14:01,180
I've never really learned.

303
00:14:01,260 --> 00:14:02,440
It's impossible for me.

304
00:14:02,620 --> 00:14:03,660
If you don't want
another year in junior high

305
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,520
what are you going to do?

306
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:11,210
You can at least go to a technical school.

307
00:14:11,290 --> 00:14:13,080
You want to be a yob out there?

308
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:13,690
Boss.

309
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:14,920
What else can you do?

310
00:14:15,010 --> 00:14:15,240
Boss.

311
00:14:15,330 --> 00:14:16,400
What?

312
00:14:17,010 --> 00:14:17,690
I mean

313
00:14:17,770 --> 00:14:18,610
the meal's getting cold.

314
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:20,600
Eat it first.

315
00:14:20,850 --> 00:14:23,150
Is it not hot enough on such a hot day?

316
00:14:25,130 --> 00:14:26,960
Don't you want to eat anymore, right?

317
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:28,170
No.

318
00:14:28,260 --> 00:14:29,520
I mean

319
00:14:30,060 --> 00:14:32,000
you have a drink first.

320
00:14:33,930 --> 00:14:35,200
Here.

321
00:14:41,940 --> 00:14:43,120
This liquor is not good.

322
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:47,400
Bring me the one in the red bottle.

323
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:51,080
Give me that red one.

324
00:14:53,210 --> 00:14:54,680
The red bottle one is better.

325
00:14:56,420 --> 00:14:58,150
I can't even drink Moutai.

326
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:03,380
Boss.

327
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:04,950
What?

328
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:08,120
I have an idea.

329
00:15:08,980 --> 00:15:10,090
What kind of idea?

330
00:15:10,180 --> 00:15:11,840
Go for his teacher.

331
00:15:51,970 --> 00:15:53,050
I'll come back to see you guys

332
00:15:53,140 --> 00:15:54,270
during my vacation.

333
00:15:54,610 --> 00:15:55,590
Remember what you said.

334
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:56,530
If you don't come back

335
00:15:56,620 --> 00:15:57,930
I'll get angry with you.

336
00:15:58,010 --> 00:15:59,800
It's just a change of school.

337
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:01,290
When you arrive at the new school

338
00:16:01,380 --> 00:16:02,630
remember to call us.

339
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:03,400
Sure.

340
00:16:03,490 --> 00:16:04,610
Mao

341
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:06,450
we will all miss you.

342
00:16:06,540 --> 00:16:07,560
Don't cry.

343
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:09,550
You make me quite sentimental.

344
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:10,890
I'm leaving.

345
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:11,860
Bye.

346
00:16:12,380 --> 00:16:13,500
Bye, Xiao.

347
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:15,900
Bye.

348
00:16:16,780 --> 00:16:17,510
I have to go.

349
00:16:17,590 --> 00:16:18,560
Goodbye.

350
00:16:23,060 --> 00:16:23,890
Bye-bye.

351
00:16:23,970 --> 00:16:25,240
Go back.

352
00:16:26,340 --> 00:16:27,360
Such a good person

353
00:16:27,610 --> 00:16:28,710
but gone all of a sudden.

354
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:30,830
Hua.

355
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:33,550
Could you not leave in the future?

356
00:16:33,890 --> 00:16:36,290
I'm already so sad when Mao is gone.

357
00:16:36,380 --> 00:16:39,250
I will definitely not be able
to bear it if you are gone.

358
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:40,690
I'm not leaving now.

359
00:16:40,780 --> 00:16:42,280
I mean in the future.

360
00:16:42,860 --> 00:16:44,210
Then be sad when the future comes.

361
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:46,290
Don't want to be sad.

362
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:47,330
Fine, I'm not leaving.

363
00:16:47,410 --> 00:16:48,930
Don't blather.

364
00:16:49,020 --> 00:16:50,030
How old are you?

365
00:16:50,170 --> 00:16:50,970
That's right.

366
00:16:51,050 --> 00:16:52,730
Hua's with us everyday

367
00:16:52,810 --> 00:16:54,170
and Mao will come back during holidays.

368
00:16:54,260 --> 00:16:55,670
Why are you crying?

369
00:16:55,940 --> 00:16:56,730
Alright, don't cry.

370
00:16:56,820 --> 00:16:58,040
I'll take you to eat something.

371
00:16:58,410 --> 00:16:59,940
Let's go.

372
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:03,450
You cry like that when Mao is gone.

373
00:17:03,540 --> 00:17:05,550
How sad will you be when I'm leaving?

374
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:07,000
If you want to go, just go.

375
00:17:07,089 --> 00:17:07,849
Who cares about you?

376
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:08,920
You...

377
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:11,290
Okay. It's alright.

378
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:12,440
When are you leaving?

379
00:17:14,490 --> 00:17:15,369
I have no idea.

380
00:17:15,780 --> 00:17:17,920
Maybe I will leave suddenly one day.

381
00:17:18,109 --> 00:17:19,609
Why suddenly?

382
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:21,510
Why don't you tell us?

383
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:23,829
I didn't mean to meddle in your affairs.

384
00:17:23,930 --> 00:17:24,810
I mean

385
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:25,970
if you don't tell us

386
00:17:26,060 --> 00:17:27,410
I'm afraid we couldn't find you.

387
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,650
If you don't want to say...

388
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:29,750
Fine, fine.

389
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:31,130
I will definitely tell you.

390
00:17:31,210 --> 00:17:32,390
I won't leave suddenly.

391
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:33,370
It's a deal.

392
00:17:33,460 --> 00:17:34,690
You promise.

393
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:35,660
I promise.

394
00:17:38,380 --> 00:17:39,790
But don't yell at me in the future.

395
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:41,360
I didn't yell.

396
00:17:43,870 --> 00:17:44,750
Fine.

397
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:46,270
Do you want to eat wonton?

398
00:17:47,490 --> 00:17:48,370
Yes.

399
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:55,220
Chen Jun He.

400
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,010
Mr Wu?

401
00:17:58,100 --> 00:17:59,000
I'm looking for you.

402
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:01,000
Why?

403
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,960
Your uncle came to me.

404
00:18:03,380 --> 00:18:04,720
For what?

405
00:18:07,100 --> 00:18:08,210
Let's find a place to talk.

406
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:09,310
What's the matter?

407
00:18:09,390 --> 00:18:10,450
Can't we just have a casual talk?

408
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:11,630
What did my uncle tell you?

409
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:12,240
Don't ask now.

410
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:13,300
I'll tell you later.

411
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:30,680
Drink on your own?

412
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,000
You want to drink, too?

413
00:18:33,340 --> 00:18:35,160
I'm 19. I can drink.

414
00:18:36,220 --> 00:18:36,970
Drink in my face.

415
00:18:37,060 --> 00:18:38,550
How dare you.

416
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:41,500
Tell me

417
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:43,960
are you at odds with
those two girls in my class?

418
00:18:44,780 --> 00:18:45,720
At odds?

419
00:18:46,220 --> 00:18:47,110
Don't play dumb.

420
00:18:47,330 --> 00:18:49,160
You came to me for this?

421
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:50,250
Talk about this first.

422
00:18:50,340 --> 00:18:51,680
I have something else to say later.

423
00:18:52,580 --> 00:18:53,370
Mr Wu

424
00:18:53,460 --> 00:18:54,650
I'm not at odds with them.

425
00:18:54,730 --> 00:18:55,760
I didn't bully them either.

426
00:18:56,020 --> 00:18:56,960
I have a clear conscience.

427
00:18:58,620 --> 00:19:00,080
OK, I will believe you once again.

428
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:02,810
If I find you bullying them again

429
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:04,070
I won't spare you.

430
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:05,830
OK.

431
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:07,040
I have graduated

432
00:19:07,130 --> 00:19:07,970
and I can't even see them.

433
00:19:08,060 --> 00:19:09,350
How am I going to bully them?

434
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,520
What if you go to my class?

435
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:12,050
Why can't you see them?

436
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:13,430
You will be classmates with them.

437
00:19:13,850 --> 00:19:14,730
What?

438
00:19:16,420 --> 00:19:17,250
How about

439
00:19:17,340 --> 00:19:18,240
you

440
00:19:18,580 --> 00:19:19,470
going to my class

441
00:19:19,620 --> 00:19:20,500
for another year?

442
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,040
My uncle let you say this to me?

443
00:19:26,170 --> 00:19:27,560
Your uncle told me that

444
00:19:27,730 --> 00:19:29,440
he wanted me to find a
technical school for you

445
00:19:29,580 --> 00:19:30,790
to learn some skills.

446
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:32,880
As long as you won't mess around all day.

447
00:19:33,260 --> 00:19:34,140
Wait.

448
00:19:34,870 --> 00:19:35,880
What do you mean?

449
00:19:35,970 --> 00:19:36,410
What do I mean?

450
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:37,720
I want you to come to my class

451
00:19:38,170 --> 00:19:40,200
and take the exam seriously again.

452
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:43,400
I have already taken
the exam. It won't work.

453
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:46,520
How can it work if you
don't even read the book?

454
00:19:46,940 --> 00:19:47,840
Chen Jun He.

455
00:19:47,970 --> 00:19:49,170
What's a real man?

456
00:19:49,260 --> 00:19:51,120
A real man carries things
through to the end.

457
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:52,470
What about you?

458
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,360
You've studied hard for so many years

459
00:19:54,450 --> 00:19:55,930
but thrown in the
sponge at the final step.

460
00:19:56,010 --> 00:19:57,190
What have you done earlier?

461
00:19:58,180 --> 00:19:58,930
I'm not going.

462
00:19:59,020 --> 00:19:59,890
You have to go.

463
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:01,270
Just give it a shot.

464
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:02,690
Come to my class

465
00:20:02,780 --> 00:20:04,040
and study as hard as you can.

466
00:20:04,130 --> 00:20:05,170
Take the exam again.

467
00:20:05,250 --> 00:20:06,610
If you fail again, you
can go and study

468
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:07,370
bulldozers, excavators

469
00:20:07,450 --> 00:20:08,330
pastries, cosmetology and so on.

470
00:20:08,420 --> 00:20:09,130
I won't stop you.

471
00:20:09,210 --> 00:20:10,360
I will find you a school.

472
00:20:10,530 --> 00:20:12,240
At least you've tried.

473
00:20:12,380 --> 00:20:13,260
Right?

474
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,690
Listen, your uncle
came to me the other day

475
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:17,550
and we each drank a catty of liquor.

476
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:19,210
I drank to tears

477
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:20,550
and felt so sorry for you.

478
00:20:20,870 --> 00:20:22,190
You can't only live for yourself

479
00:20:22,340 --> 00:20:24,270
in your whole life.

480
00:20:24,580 --> 00:20:26,590
You also have to live
for those who love you.

481
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:28,330
If you let your family down,

482
00:20:28,420 --> 00:20:29,870
what kind of man would you be?

483
00:20:35,340 --> 00:20:36,220
I'll wait for you.

484
00:20:47,370 --> 00:20:50,900
[Harbin Aeronautical Institute is
Accepting Trainees]

485
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:03,020
Why is this room empty?

486
00:21:03,110 --> 00:21:03,930
Nonsense.

487
00:21:04,010 --> 00:21:04,970
It must be empty.

488
00:21:05,060 --> 00:21:06,120
Why?

489
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:16,730
Tell me,

490
00:21:16,820 --> 00:21:18,050
what can

491
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:19,440
you kids do?

492
00:21:20,260 --> 00:21:22,150
At least your Du told you.

493
00:21:22,780 --> 00:21:24,030
My child

494
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:25,600
didn't even tell us.

495
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:26,900
I was wondering

496
00:21:26,990 --> 00:21:29,300
what review materials
cost so much money.

497
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:30,170
Fan Shui Shui

498
00:21:30,260 --> 00:21:31,080
I'm telling you

499
00:21:31,170 --> 00:21:32,810
don't think of taking a
penny from me in the future.

500
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:33,910
You know?

501
00:21:34,220 --> 00:21:35,560
I was afraid

502
00:21:35,690 --> 00:21:37,510
you wouldn't let me go if I told you.

503
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,170
If you hadn't gone

504
00:21:38,260 --> 00:21:39,690
you couldn't have been cheated.

505
00:21:39,770 --> 00:21:40,890
Believe it or not, I dare to fix you.

506
00:21:40,970 --> 00:21:41,200
Hold on.

507
00:21:41,290 --> 00:21:42,050
Sister.

508
00:21:42,140 --> 00:21:43,280
The child is too old to be spanked.

509
00:21:43,370 --> 00:21:43,720
Right?

510
00:21:43,810 --> 00:21:44,650
Especially for girls.

511
00:21:44,740 --> 00:21:45,910
You can't spank a girl.

512
00:21:46,570 --> 00:21:48,050
This is too irritating.

513
00:21:48,130 --> 00:21:50,320
It won't be so hard to even raise a boy.

514
00:21:50,410 --> 00:21:51,170
Wait.

515
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:53,190
Let's see how your
father will fix you tonight.

516
00:21:53,610 --> 00:21:54,270
Aunt,

517
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:55,030
we were...

518
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:56,030
Shut up.

519
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:58,670
Where did your money come from?

520
00:22:00,450 --> 00:22:01,750
I am asking you.

521
00:22:02,110 --> 00:22:03,200
Tell me.

522
00:22:03,290 --> 00:22:05,000
Didn't you tell me to shut up?

523
00:22:05,540 --> 00:22:07,830
I think you are asking for trouble.

524
00:22:07,930 --> 00:22:09,330
Have I been too good to you these days?

525
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:10,170
Didn't we just mention

526
00:22:10,250 --> 00:22:11,400
not to punish girls?

527
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:13,210
Don't shout at her.

528
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:14,450
We just mentioned that

529
00:22:14,530 --> 00:22:15,750
you can't spank a girl.

530
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:16,720
Li Qing Tong.

531
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:17,930
Just wait.

532
00:22:18,020 --> 00:22:19,370
Let's go home and
settle the bill together.

533
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:19,850
Wait.

534
00:22:19,930 --> 00:22:21,770
I want to say something to you.

535
00:22:21,860 --> 00:22:22,920
This is too shameful.

536
00:22:23,260 --> 00:22:24,840
You guys are not kids anymore.

537
00:22:24,940 --> 00:22:25,640
Why are you so brainless

538
00:22:25,730 --> 00:22:27,190
to believe people like that?

539
00:22:27,610 --> 00:22:30,590
Can the flight attendant be
appointed with some money?

540
00:22:30,860 --> 00:22:31,570
Moreover

541
00:22:31,660 --> 00:22:33,490
it's wrong to hide it from us.

542
00:22:33,570 --> 00:22:34,530
If you encountered a child trafficker

543
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:35,730
and sold you to the mountains

544
00:22:35,820 --> 00:22:37,490
you would still count money for them.

545
00:22:37,580 --> 00:22:39,080
This stupid child of mine

546
00:22:39,170 --> 00:22:40,650
should be sold out.

547
00:22:40,730 --> 00:22:42,560
I'm done with raising her.

548
00:22:42,860 --> 00:22:44,230
It's not that bad.

549
00:22:45,060 --> 00:22:45,680
You're back, brother.

550
00:22:45,770 --> 00:22:46,870
How's it?

551
00:22:47,620 --> 00:22:48,250
Don't worry.

552
00:22:48,340 --> 00:22:49,440
I have asked.

553
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:50,690
That's indeed a swindler

554
00:22:50,780 --> 00:22:52,200
and has collected quite a lot of money.

555
00:22:52,660 --> 00:22:54,290
The police have filed a case.

556
00:22:54,370 --> 00:22:55,050
This guy will definitely be caught.

557
00:22:55,130 --> 00:22:55,650
That's OK.

558
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:56,450
By that time,

559
00:22:56,540 --> 00:22:57,440
the money can be returned.

560
00:22:57,530 --> 00:22:58,840
That will be fine.

561
00:22:58,970 --> 00:23:00,490
500 yuan is no big deal

562
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:01,930
but lying to your parents

563
00:23:02,020 --> 00:23:03,330
is too bad in nature.

564
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:04,400
Right.

565
00:23:04,490 --> 00:23:05,440
Wait.

566
00:23:05,740 --> 00:23:06,990
500 yuan?

567
00:23:07,380 --> 00:23:08,070
Wang Xiao Min.

568
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:09,110
Mum, help me.

569
00:23:09,260 --> 00:23:10,520
Brother

570
00:23:11,060 --> 00:23:11,760
don't hit him.

571
00:23:11,850 --> 00:23:12,450
Aunt.

572
00:23:12,530 --> 00:23:14,120
Calm down.

573
00:23:19,010 --> 00:23:20,360
I couldn't become a flight attendant

574
00:23:20,740 --> 00:23:22,400
and got beaten up.

575
00:23:22,970 --> 00:23:24,880
All my pocket money was confiscated.

576
